{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"match","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"stringLength"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"string"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringReversed","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Passing the correct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":", this is more efficient if the reversed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match"},{"type":"text","text":"] will only construct it if the compiled pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires reverse matches."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not be obtained by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.strreverse"},{"text":"]. This works only if the string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","title":"match(stringLength:string:stringReversed:)","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"match"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"stringReversed","k